<i>¤  Yeah, Twisterella ¤¤</i>

1000
01:09:37,706 --> 01:09:40,732
<i>[ Explosion ]

1001
01:09:43,946 --> 01:09:46,574
- [ Gasps ] Billy !
- Hello, darling.

1002
01:09:46,649 --> 01:09:49,209
I've been waiting outside
for half an hour.

1003
01:09:49,285 --> 01:09:52,721
I said I'd see you inside.
Come on. Let's dance, anyway.

1004
01:09:52,788 --> 01:09:55,279
- <i>[ Laughter ]
- I like it.

1005
01:09:55,391 --> 01:09:57,723
This is my song.
Me and Arthur wrote it.

1006
01:09:57,793 --> 01:10:00,887
- Did you, pet ?
- Yeah. It's the first
time they've played it.

1007
01:10:00,963 --> 01:10:03,727
- I can't do it.
- Of course you can.

1008
01:10:03,799 --> 01:10:06,563
- Like this with your legs.
- What do you do with your feet ?

1009
01:10:06,635 --> 01:10:08,500
- With your hips.
- No, pet. Come on.

1010
01:10:08,604 --> 01:10:11,004
Let's have an orange squash.
Come on.

1011
01:10:11,273 --> 01:10:13,241
<i>¤ But she doesn't mind at all ¤</i>

1012
01:10:13,309 --> 01:10:16,642
<i>¤ She's Twisterella</i>
<i>Yeah, Twisterella ¤</i>

1013
01:10:16,745 --> 01:10:19,612
Oh, look what crawled out
of the corned beef!

1014
01:10:19,715 --> 01:10:22,240
<i>-¤Kookie Twisterella ¤</i>
- Hello, Rita.

1015
01:10:22,318 --> 01:10:24,878
<i>-¤She hasn't got a fella ¤</i>
- I don't think you've met Barbara.

1016
01:10:24,987 --> 01:10:27,922
<i>-¤ The kids all have a ball ¤</i>
- Barbara, this is Rita.

1017
01:10:27,990 --> 01:10:30,891
<i>-¤But she doesn't mind at all</i>
<i>She's Twisterella ¤</i>
- <i>Rita, this is Barbara.</i>

1018
01:10:30,993 --> 01:10:33,962
I'm very glad you've come, because
I think I owe you a word of explanation.

1019
01:10:34,029 --> 01:10:37,726
A word of explanation ? Just get back
in the cheese with the other maggots.

1020
01:10:37,833 --> 01:10:39,960
Will you kindly tell me
who this girl is ?

1021
01:10:40,236 --> 01:10:42,033
Oh, get Madam Fancy Knickers !

1022
01:10:42,304 --> 01:10:44,272
I suppose
she's your rotten sister.

1023
01:10:44,373 --> 01:10:46,773
I thought she was
in a rotten iron lung !

1024
01:10:46,842 --> 01:10:49,640
For your information,
I happen to be Billy's fiancee.

1025
01:10:49,712 --> 01:10:52,647
Well, for your information,
he happens to be engaged to me !

1026
01:10:52,715 --> 01:10:55,707
- In front of a witness !
- I think I can explain all of this.

1027
01:10:55,818 --> 01:10:58,912
Explain till you're blue in the rotten
face. It'll make no difference to me.

1028
01:10:59,021 --> 01:11:01,785
I realize this must all seem
very confusing to you, Rita.

1029
01:11:01,857 --> 01:11:04,792
But I thought Barbara
had broken the engagement off.

1030
01:11:04,860 --> 01:11:06,851
- Billy !
- <i>You gave that ring to me!</i>

1031
01:11:06,929 --> 01:11:10,262
- Well, there's been
a bit of a mix-up, Rita.
- Yeah, there has.

1032
01:11:10,366 --> 01:11:14,803
Well, you don't handle the goods unless
you intend to buy. Ooh, you're rotten.

1033
01:11:14,903 --> 01:11:17,701
Does this mean you're
breaking the engagement off?

1034
01:11:17,806 --> 01:11:20,639
You don't get off it like that !
I want that ring !

1035
01:11:20,709 --> 01:11:22,643
I've got to know !

1036
01:11:22,711 --> 01:11:25,544
Have you been having
relations with this girl ?

1037
01:11:25,648 --> 01:11:29,311
What do you think he's been doing ?
Knitting a pullover ?

1038
01:11:29,418 --> 01:11:31,352
Give me that ring !
It's mine !

1039
01:11:31,453 --> 01:11:34,786
I shall give the ring back
if and when I break off the engagement.

1040
01:11:34,890 --> 01:11:37,688
- Are you gonna give me that ring ?
- <i>Don't you threaten me!</i>

1041
01:11:37,760 --> 01:11:40,661
I won't threaten you.
I'll flatten you. Take off that ring !

1042
01:11:40,729 --> 01:11:43,527
- No ! It's mine !
- Give it to me !

1043
01:11:43,599 --> 01:11:45,863
- <i>Give it to me!</i>
- Right. Come on, Gerry.

1044
01:11:45,968 --> 01:11:49,062
[ Crowd Shouting ]

1045
01:11:49,338 --> 01:11:52,637
- No ! Let me go !
- Give me that ring ! It's mine !

1046
01:11:54,310 --> 01:11:57,939
You've had it, Fisher mate.
You've had it.

1047
01:11:58,047 --> 01:12:00,106
[ Drum Roll ]

1048
01:12:00,382 --> 01:12:03,749
Ladies and gentlemen, that last number
we just played was called " Twisterella."

1049
01:12:03,852 --> 01:12:07,379
It's a brand-new one, and it's written
by two of our local boys here,

1050
01:12:07,489 --> 01:12:10,515
Arthur Crabtree--
here's Arthur--

1051
01:12:10,592 --> 01:12:13,117
<i>[ Applause ]

1052
01:12:14,663 --> 01:12:16,824
and his colleague Billy Fisher.

1053
01:12:16,899 --> 01:12:18,924
Billy's somewhere
in the hall, I know.

1054
01:12:19,034 --> 01:12:21,730
<i>He's probably celebrating some</i>
<i>wonderful news he's had today.</i>

1055
01:12:21,837 --> 01:12:25,364
- There he is.
- Billy Fisher. The man himself!

1056
01:12:25,474 --> 01:12:27,669
Congratulations, Billy.

1057
01:12:27,743 --> 01:12:30,439
We just heard of your
wonderful job in London...

1058
01:12:30,546 --> 01:12:33,640
<i>writing scripts</i>
<i>for comedian Danny Boon.</i>

1059
01:12:33,749 --> 01:12:36,411
<i>Congratulations</i>
<i>and best of luck.</i>

1060
01:12:36,518 --> 01:12:39,009
- Billy Liar !
- <i>[ Crowd Whistling ]

1061
01:12:39,088 --> 01:12:41,079
[ Crowd Cheering ]

1062
01:12:41,357 --> 01:12:43,154
<i>[ Whistling Continues ]

1063
01:12:43,425 --> 01:12:46,519
<i>Ladies and gentlemen,</i>
<i>start with us the conga.</i>

1064
01:12:46,595 --> 01:12:48,995
<i>¤ ¤[ Conga ]

1065
01:12:49,098 --> 01:12:51,623
Stupid ! What do you want
to tell 'em that for ?

1066
01:12:51,734 --> 01:12:54,669
- Why not ?
