what you want to do as well.

1068
01:12:57,506 --> 01:13:00,566
'Cause listen, I don't know what tale
you've been telling my mother...

1069
01:13:00,676 --> 01:13:02,803
about Barbara being
this sister of yours,

1070
01:13:02,911 --> 01:13:06,369
but she's been going on at me
all afternoon, so just pack it in...

1071
01:13:06,448 --> 01:13:08,507
and grow up !

1072
01:13:08,617 --> 01:13:11,450
¤¤ [ Conga Continues ]

1073
01:13:36,712 --> 01:13:40,512
[ Laughter]

1074
01:13:51,460 --> 01:13:54,554
<i>[ Man On Speaker ] Mr. William Fisher</i>
<i>wanted on the telephone, please.</i>

1075
01:13:54,663 --> 01:13:57,962
<i>Mr. William Fisher!</i>

1076
01:13:58,033 --> 01:14:00,831
Mr. William Fisher
wanted on the telephone.

1077
01:14:03,071 --> 01:14:05,801
Let's go.

1078
01:14:13,449 --> 01:14:16,612
<i>Can Mr. William Fisher</i>
<i>please come to the telephone ?

1079
01:14:16,685 --> 01:14:18,744
<i>Thank you.</i>

1080
01:14:25,561 --> 01:14:29,224
Liz, do you find life difficult ?

1081
01:14:29,498 --> 01:14:34,162
You know, I wish it were something
you could turn off and start again.

1082
01:14:34,236 --> 01:14:38,104
You know, like starting
a new page in an exercise book.

1083
01:14:38,207 --> 01:14:41,699
It's been done.
Turning over a new leaf.

1084
01:14:41,777 --> 01:14:44,177
I turn over
a new leaf every day,

1085
01:14:44,246 --> 01:14:46,908
but the blots show through.

1086
01:14:49,184 --> 01:14:51,744
Billy, who do you love ?

1087
01:14:51,854 --> 01:14:53,754
Thee, lass.

1088
01:14:53,856 --> 01:14:56,689
- Yes, it sounds like it, doesn't it ?
- I do, Liz, I do.

1089
01:14:56,758 --> 01:14:58,726
Say it properly, then.

1090
01:15:00,963 --> 01:15:03,158
Well, I do, Liz, I do.

1091
01:15:03,232 --> 01:15:06,998
- I want to marry you, you know, Billy ?
- I get engaged too often.

1092
01:15:07,069 --> 01:15:10,232
I don't want to get engaged.
I want to get married.

1093
01:15:10,506 --> 01:15:13,532
Well, uh, we will one day.

1094
01:15:13,642 --> 01:15:16,543
Yes... one day.

1095
01:15:23,018 --> 01:15:25,316
- <i>Billy?</i>
- <i>What ?

1096
01:15:25,587 --> 01:15:30,183
<i>You know,you know what you</i>
<i>wanted me to do that night ?

1097
01:15:30,259 --> 01:15:33,126
<i>When we were walking</i>
<i>through the park.</i>

1098
01:15:33,228 --> 01:15:35,856
And I said another night.

1099
01:15:35,964 --> 01:15:37,898
Yes.

1100
01:15:37,966 --> 01:15:40,230
Well, it's another night
tonight, isn't it ?

1101
01:15:40,335 --> 01:15:42,701
- Are you sure ?
- Yes.

1102
01:15:42,771 --> 01:15:45,638
Uh, well, what-what--

1103
01:15:53,348 --> 01:15:56,249
- Billy ?
- Mm-hmm ?

1104
01:15:57,619 --> 01:16:00,611
You know there have been
others, don't you ?

1105
01:16:00,722 --> 01:16:05,557
Oh, well, I somehow imagined
that there might have been.

1106
01:16:05,627 --> 01:16:08,357
- Shall I tell you about them ?
- No, no.

1107
01:16:13,135 --> 01:16:15,296
Well, go on, then.
Tell me about it.

1108
01:16:15,571 --> 01:16:18,062
- No, not now.
- No, tell me about it.

1109
01:16:18,173 --> 01:16:21,108
- You think that's why
I'm always going away ?
- I don't know.

1110
01:16:21,176 --> 01:16:24,043
- <i>[ Bell Tolling ]</i>
- Oh, it's not that.

1111
01:16:24,146 --> 01:16:27,809
It's-- Sometimes
I want to go away.

1112
01:16:27,916 --> 01:16:30,885
It's not you, Billy.
It's this town.

1113
01:16:30,953 --> 01:16:34,980
It's the people we know.
I don't like knowing everybody.

1114
01:16:35,090 --> 01:16:37,183
I don't like becoming
a part of things.

1115
01:16:37,292 --> 01:16:40,261
- Don't you know what I mean ?
- Yes, I do, Liz. I do.

1116
01:16:40,329 --> 01:16:42,991
What I'd like to be is invisible.

1117
01:16:43,098 --> 01:16:46,090
I'd like to be able to move around
without having to explain anything.

1118
01:16:46,201 --> 01:16:49,830
Liz, listen. Do you know what I do
when I want to feel invisible ?

1119
01:16:49,938 --> 01:16:52,270
Well, I've never told anybody before.

1120
01:16:52,341 --> 01:16:56,277
I have a sort of-- well,
it's an imaginary country where I go.

1121
01:16:56,345 --> 01:17:00,008
- It has its own people.
- Do you do that ? I knew you would.

1122
01:17:00,115 --> 01:17:03,346
Oh, Billy, why are we so alike ? You
know I can read your thoughts. Town--

1123
01:17:03,619 --> 01:17:06,315
Oh, no, no, no. This is more
than a town. It's a whole country.

1124
01:17:06,388 --> 01:17:09,380
I'm supposed to be the prime minister,
and you're the foreign secretary.

1125
01:17:09,658 --> 01:17:11,922
- Oh, thank you.
- I think about it for hours.

1126
01:17:11,994 --> 01:17:16,090
Sometimes I think if we were married,
with a house of our own,

1127
01:17:16,164 --> 01:17:19,292
we could just sit
and imagine ourselves there.

1128
01:17:19,401 --> 01:17:24,031
- Yes, we could.
- I want a room in the house
with a green/beige door.

1129
01:17:24,139 --> 01:17:27,336
It will be a big room, and when
we go in it through the door, that's it.

1130
01:17:27,442 --> 01:17:30,377
That's our country.
Nobody else will be allowed in at all.

1131
01:17:30,646 --> 01:17:34,207
And I thought we could make models of
the principal cities out of cardboard...

1132
01:17:34,316 --> 01:17:36,045
and have toy soldiers
painted for the people.

1133
01:17:36,151 --> 01:17:40,747
We can draw maps. In the afternoon,
we could go there and nobody'd find us.

1134
01:17:40,856 --> 01:17:42,881
We could design
our own newspapers.

1135
01:17:42,991 --> 01:17:45,983
We could make uniforms if we wanted to.
It will be our country.

1136
01:17:46,061 --> 01:17:49,030
Let's have a model train
that the kids won't be allowed to use.

1137
01:17:49,131 --> 01:17:51,895
Oh, Liz, Liz,
will you marry me ?

1138
01:17:52,000 --> 01:17:53,831
Yes, Billy.

1139
01:18:06,448 --> 01:18:09,383
[ Stifled Laughter]

1140
01:18:12,454 --> 01:18:15,014
- Oh, Liz.
- <i>[ Laughter Continues ]

1141
01:18:15,123 --> 01:18:17,819
- What is it ?
- It's nothing.

1142
01:18:19,194 --> 01:18:21,094
[ Whistling ]

1143
01:18:21,196 --> 01:18:23,096
[ Squawking ]

1144
01:18:23,198 --> 01:18:25,689
[ Laughter Continues ]

1145
01:18:25,767 --> 01:18:28,998
Whoever's out there
is gonna get their bastard teeth
knocked down their throat !

1146
01:18:29,071 --> 01:18:33,064
[ Mocking ] " I'm the prime minister,
and you're the foreign secretary."

1147
01:18:33,175 --> 01:18:36,474
Leave them, Billy.
Oh, leave them.

1148
01:18:36,745 --> 01:18:39,908
[ Laughing, Chattering ]

1149
01:18:41,516 --> 01:18:45,714
They're not worth it.
The whole place isn't worth it.

1150
01:18:45,787 --> 01:18:48,779
[ Chattering Continues ]

1151
01:18:51,760 --> 01:18:54,024
Bastards.
[ Sighs ]

1152
01:18:54,096 --> 01:18:59,329
Look, Billy, why don't you go
to London ? I'll come with you.

1153
01:18:59,434 --> 01:19:03,234
Oh, it would be
marvelous if we could.

1154
01:19:03,305 --> 01:19:06,968
But we can, Billy, we can.
What's there to stop us ?

1155
01:19:07,075 --> 01:19:10,135
- There are all sorts
of arrangements to make.
- No, there's not.

1156
01:19:10,245 --> 01:19:13,806
You just buy a ticket and get
on a train. That's all you have to do.

1157
01:19:13,915 --> 01:19:16,884
- Well, you can't just go.
- Yes, you can. We could go tonight.

1158
01:19:16,952 --> 01:19:20,149
- There's a midnight train.
It gets into London at 7:00.
- What, tonight, Liz ?

1159
01:19:20,255 --> 01:19:24,282
Yes, 12:05 from Central Station.
We'll be in London tomorrow.

1160
01:19:24,392 --> 01:19:28,089
Breakfast at Lyon's.
Hyde Park in the afternoon.

1161
01:19:28,163 --> 01:19:30,495
Piccadilly tomorrow evening.

1162
01:19:30,766 --> 01:19:34,031
- Look, what time is it ?
- l-It's just after 10:00.

1163
01:19:35,470 --> 01:19:37,768
I'm going, Billy.
Are you coming with me ?

1164
01:19:40,175 --> 01:19:42,473
- Yes, Liz, I'm coming.
- Are you sure ?

1165
01:19:42,577 --> 01:19:44,477
I'm coming with you.

1166
01:19:44,579 --> 01:19:47,946
Right. I'll meet you at the barrier
at about 12:00, all right ?

1167
01:19:48,016 --> 01:19:50,780
- Fine, yeah.
- What are you gonna tell
your father and mother ?

1168
01:19:50,886 --> 01:19:53,218
Oh, they know about it
already, more or less.

1169
01:19:53,321 --> 01:19:56,222
- Billy, you won't
let me down, will you ?
- No, of course I won't.

1170
01:19:56,324 --> 01:20:00,090
We're going to London !

1171
01:20:00,162 --> 01:20:04,394
Father, the men--
they're coming up the drive !

1172
01:20:04,499 --> 01:20:07,024
[ Both Laughing ]

1173
01:20:26,087 --> 01:20:29,215
Yeah. Oh, I see.

1174
01:20:30,926 --> 01:20:33,861
Oh, oh, I see.
She's still with her, is she ?

1175
01:20:33,962 --> 01:20:36,829
Right.
Thank you very much. Good-bye.

1176
01:20:42,938 --> 01:20:45,566
Well, what time of night
do you call this ?

1177
01:20:45,841 --> 01:20:48,935
It's only 10:00. Why ?
Do you want some chips bring in ?

1178
01:20:49,010 --> 01:20:52,138
Never mind chips.
They're down at the infirmary.

1179
01:20:52,214 --> 01:20:55,081
- Who ?
- You mother and your grandmother.
Who the hell do you think ?

1180
01:20:55,183 --> 01:20:58,084
<i>Your grandmother's</i>
<i>been taken badly again.</i>

1181
01:20:58,186 --> 01:21:00,120
Why ? What's up with her ?

1182
01:21:00,188 --> 01:21:02,656
<i>What's always up with her?</i>
<i>You should know.</i>

1183
01:21:02,924 --> 01:21:06,951
<i>I've been ringing that bloody</i>
<i>dance hall for the past hour,</i>
<i>trying to get word to you.</i>

1184
01:21:07,028 --> 01:21:09,929
<i>Why don't you go</i>
<i>where you say you're going ?

1185
01:21:10,031 --> 01:21:12,090
Is it serious or something ?

1186
01:21:12,200 --> 01:21:14,600
Your mother wants you
down at the infirmary.

1187
01:21:14,870 --> 01:21:18,203
Go on.
Go on and get yourself a taxi ordered.

1188
01:21:27,315 --> 01:21:29,613
<i>[ Dialing Phone ]

1189
01:21:36,124 --> 01:21:38,490
Hello. Speedway Taxis ?

1190
01:21:38,560 --> 01:21:42,189
Could you send a cab
to 23 Ringway Crescent, please ?

1191
01:21:42,297 --> 01:21:45,266
It's to go to the infirmary.

1192
01:21:46,635 --> 01:21:49,195
Oh, good, good. Thank you.

1193
01:21:51,039 --> 01:21:53,200
Be about ten minutes.

1194
01:21:53,308 --> 01:21:55,674
- You don't go up there.
- I'm just--

1195
01:21:55,911 --> 01:21:58,505
- You don't go up there, I said.
- I'm just gonna get washed.

1196
01:21:58,580 --> 01:22:01,378
Well, you can stop looking.
You don't go up there.

1197
01:22:01,449 --> 01:22:05,715
I'm fed up with you, with your
idling and your meddling ways
and all of the things besides.

1198
01:22:05,954 --> 01:22:07,649
- What's up ?
-" What's up ?"

1199
01:22:07,923 --> 01:22:10,414
- <i>What did you do with that</i>
<i>letter of your mother's ?
- What letter ?

1200
01:22:10,525 --> 01:22:13,119
- <i>That letter that you</i>
<i>promised to post for her.</i>
- I posted it.

1201
01:22:13,228 --> 01:22:15,128
You posted bloody nothing !

1202
01:22:15,230 --> 01:22:18,358
[ Nervous Chuckle ] l-I did post it.
That's just the rough copy.

1203
01:22:18,433 --> 01:22:21,561
Don't tell me your lies.
I found it upstairs in the wardrobe.

1204
01:22:21,670 --> 01:22:24,070
- <i>Hey, and what about</i>
<i>them calendars as well?</i>
- What calendars ?

1205
01:22:24,172 --> 01:22:27,608
I'll give you what if you don't stop
saying " what" to me, young man.

1206
01:22:27,709 --> 01:22:30,269
You can't keep your hands
off nothing, can you ?

1207
01:22:30,345 --> 01:22:32,643
I've got it all
from Councilor Duxbury.

1208
01:22:32,747 --> 01:22:35,272
What have you been doing
with their petty cash ?

1209
01:22:35,383 --> 01:22:37,943
And where is that monkey
wrench out of my garage ?

1210
01:22:38,019 --> 01:22:40,351
What would I want
with a monkey wrench ?

1211
01:22:40,455 --> 01:22:43,481
What do you want with 200 calendars ?
You're not right in your head !

1212
01:22:43,591 --> 01:22:46,958
- [ Indistinct Shouting ]
- Don't bloody shout at me !

1213
01:22:47,062 --> 01:22:50,293
- I'll knock you into next week !
- God give me strength.

1214
01:22:50,398 --> 01:22:52,662
Strength ! He wants
to give you some sense.

1215
01:22:52,767 --> 01:22:56,669
You're like a bloody Mary Ann.
You ought to be grateful
you've got a job in an office.

1216
01:22:56,771 --> 01:23:00,730
Grateful, grateful !
Grateful for this, for that !
That's all I've ever heard !

1217
01:23:01,009 --> 01:23:04,445
Grateful you let me go
to the grammar school since
the first day I went there !

1218
01:23:04,546 --> 01:23:07,982
- It's a chance we never had !
- And don't we bloody well know it ?

1219
01:23:08,083 --> 01:23:10,711
I've got to be grateful
for winning my own scholarship !

1220
01:23:10,986 --> 01:23:13,682
And what did you say when I came
running home to tell you I'd won it ?

1221
01:23:13,788 --> 01:23:16,484
<i>That you'd have to pay for the uniform,</i>
<i>and I ought to be grateful!</i>

1222
01:23:16,591 --> 01:23:19,287
And I'm supposed to be grateful
to Shadrack and Duxbury...

1223
01:23:19,394 --> 01:23:22,192
for letting me sit in one of their
rotten, stinking desks all day !

1224
01:23:22,297 --> 01:23:25,733
Well, you took the job on, and you'll
stop it when all that money's paid back.

1225
01:23:26,001 --> 01:23:28,128
- I'm not. I'm leaving.
- What do you mean, you're leaving ?

1226
01:23:28,203 --> 01:23:30,797
- I'm going to London.
- What the hell do you think
you can do in London ?

1227
01:23:31,072 --> 01:23:33,370
- Write scripts.
- Don't talk so bloody wet.

1228
01:23:33,475 --> 01:23:36,342
You ought to do a proper day's work.
Who's gonna run this business ?

1229
01:23:36,444 --> 01:23:39,072
You once told me you didn't
want me in the business !

1230
01:23:39,180 --> 01:23:41,614
Only because you were
too bloody idle, that's all.

1231
01:23:41,716 --> 01:23:44,207
Somebody's got to carry it on !
Who's gonna keep your mother ?

1232
01:23:44,319 --> 01:23:46,480
- You're not retiring, are you ?
- I'll give you a kick up your backside.

1233
01:23:46,554 --> 01:23:48,488
I'm not arguing about it.
I'm going.

1234
01:23:48,556 --> 01:23:50,820
Go, then.
I'm finished with you.

1235
01:23:51,059 --> 01:23:54,392
And don't think you're gonna take
my suitcase with you, either.

1236
01:23:54,496 --> 01:23:57,363
<i>[ Door Slams ]

1237
01:24:03,538 --> 01:24:07,565
[ Woman Sighs ] My husband had
a bad accident three years back.

1238
01:24:07,675 --> 01:24:11,509
- Did he ?
- He's all right now, but at the time--

1239
01:24:14,582 --> 01:24:16,846
We looked all over for you, lad.

1240
01:24:17,118 --> 01:24:19,450
- Where's me grandma ?
- In there.

1241
01:24:19,554 --> 01:24:22,580
They've got that black doctor to her.
She can't talk.

1242
01:24:22,690 --> 01:24:24,658
We're just waiting.

1243
01:24:24,759 --> 01:24:27,250
<i>[ Woman Coughing ]

1244
01:24:29,064 --> 01:24:31,692
She was all right
just after you went out.

1245
01:24:31,766 --> 01:24:35,202
Then when your father came home,
we were all just watching television...

1246
01:24:35,270 --> 01:24:38,171
and she slumps forward
in her chair...

1247
01:24:38,239 --> 01:24:42,767
and she started to slaver,
just like a--just like a baby.

1248
01:24:42,877 --> 01:24:44,845
Will she be all right ?

1249
01:24:45,080 --> 01:24:49,244
I don't know, lad.
I... don't know.

1250
01:24:53,888 --> 01:24:58,222
Well, you've got yourself
into a fine mess, haven't you ?

1251
01:24:58,326 --> 01:25:00,385
So it would seem.

1252
01:25:00,495 --> 01:25:04,158
I'm only thankful
she knows nothing about it.

1253
01:25:04,265 --> 01:25:08,497
Why didn't you post that letter of mine
to " Housewives' Choice" ?

1254
01:25:08,570 --> 01:25:11,903
I did post it.
I just wrote it out again, that's all.

1255
01:25:12,173 --> 01:25:15,267
- What for ?
- There was some mistakes in it.

1256
01:25:15,376 --> 01:25:20,143
I thought it would stand a better chance
if it was more grammatical, that's all.

1257
01:25:20,248 --> 01:25:22,808
Well, we can't all
be Shakespeares, can we ?

1258
01:25:22,917 --> 01:25:26,751
Anyway, we're going to sit down tomorrow
and go over everything you've done...

1259
01:25:26,821 --> 01:25:28,812
and everything you've taken.

1260
01:25:28,923 --> 01:25:31,448
Yes, well,
I won't be here tomorrow.

1261
01:25:31,559 --> 01:25:34,687
- How do you mean ?
- I'm going to London.

1262
01:25:34,762 --> 01:25:39,222
I'd have been to the station already,
well, if it hadn't been for Grandma.

1263
01:25:39,300 --> 01:25:41,825
If you're in any more
trouble, Billy,

1264
01:25:41,936 --> 01:25:44,666
it's not something you can
leave behind you, you know ?

1265
01:25:44,772 --> 01:25:47,400
You put it in your suitcase,
and you take it with you.

1266
01:25:47,475 --> 01:25:51,309
Mother, I said I'm going,
and I'm definitely going.

1267
01:25:53,615 --> 01:25:56,948
Mrs. Fisher, would you
come this way, please ?

1268
01:25:59,621 --> 01:26:01,953
<i>[ Woman Coughing ]

1269
01:26:10,331 --> 01:26:12,799
[ Sighs ]

1270
01:26:17,205 --> 01:26:19,400
<i>[ Billy's Voice ]
<i>"Three passengers on a Belfast plane....</i>

1271
01:26:19,474 --> 01:26:22,341
<i>"were Mr. Goose, Mr. Gander</i>
<i>and the Reverend Mr. Gosling.</i>

1272
01:26:22,443 --> 01:26:25,173
<i>They did not know each other. "

1273
01:26:27,482 --> 01:26:29,677
<i>The Lord is my shepherd,:</i>
<i>I shall not want.</i>

1274
01:26:29,784 --> 01:26:31,911
<i>He maketh me to lie down</i>
<i>in green pastures.</i>

1275
01:26:31,986 --> 01:26:34,921
<i>[ Women Chattering ]

1276
01:26:41,596 --> 01:26:43,530
<i>[ Woman Coughing ]

1277
01:26:43,631 --> 01:26:45,690
- Tea ?
- Please.

1278
01:26:48,269 --> 01:26:50,760
- Sixpence.
- All right.

1279
01:26:51,839 --> 01:26:53,773
Ta.

1280
01:27:03,351 --> 01:27:05,546
<i>[ Quiet Chattering ]

1281
01:27:15,029 --> 01:27:18,624
Your grandma died
at seven minutes past eleven.

1282
01:27:30,778 --> 01:27:32,712
It's hot.

1283
01:27:32,780 --> 01:27:36,238
- Do you want to go in and see her ?
- Uh, no.

1284
01:27:41,723 --> 01:27:43,748
I can't drink it.

1285
01:27:49,063 --> 01:27:52,430
What time train
you're supposed to be catching ?

1286
01:27:52,533 --> 01:27:54,558
Around midnight.

1287
01:27:57,005 --> 01:27:59,974
So... I've got to go...

1288
01:28:00,074 --> 01:28:02,702
or I won't catch it.

1289
01:28:05,013 --> 01:28:06,947
You haven't got any money.

1290
01:28:07,048 --> 01:28:10,017
Yes, I have. I've managed
to save a few pounds.

1291
01:28:12,620 --> 01:28:14,554
Do you want me to get you a taxi ?

1292
01:28:14,622 --> 01:28:17,591
No. I've got some papers
to sign first.

1293
01:28:19,494 --> 01:28:24,522
We don't say much, but--
but we need you at home, lad.

1294
01:28:24,599 --> 01:28:28,091
Yes, well, I mean, l--
I won't be away for long.

1295
01:28:28,369 --> 01:28:31,497
I'll-- You know,
I'll just get fixed up.

1296
01:28:31,606 --> 01:28:34,074
Well, I can come home next weekend.

1297
01:28:37,745 --> 01:28:40,543
See, I've got to go,
or I'll miss the train.

1298
01:28:55,029 --> 01:28:57,623
I'm sorry about me grandma.

1299
01:29:15,149 --> 01:29:17,947
<i>¤ ¤[ Drum Cadence ]

1300
01:29:28,663 --> 01:29:32,690
Officers and gentlemen
of the Ambrosian Militia,

1301
01:29:32,800 --> 01:29:36,759
we are assembled here
at the graveside...

1302
01:29:36,871 --> 01:29:39,032
to pay our respects to a great lady.

1303
01:29:40,875 --> 01:29:43,139
<i>There are many of us</i>
<i>who would not be here today...</i>

1304
01:29:43,378 --> 01:29:46,176
<i>but for her tender mercies.</i>

1305
01:29:46,447 --> 01:29:51,180
Although in her later years
she was limbless from the waist down,

1306
01:29:51,452 --> 01:29:56,014
she struggled valiantly
to combat ignorance and disease.

1307
01:29:56,124 --> 01:29:59,491
Although she will be
remembered by the world...

1308
01:29:59,560 --> 01:30:02,620
as the inventor
of penicillin and radium,

1309
01:30:02,730 --> 01:30:06,530
we of this proud regiment...

1310
01:30:06,634 --> 01:30:10,161
will remember her as our friend,

1311
01:30:10,438 --> 01:30:12,963
the Lady of the Lamb.

1312
01:30:13,074 --> 01:30:15,838
- <i>[ Drums ]
- [ Gunshots ]

1313
01:30:28,990 --> 01:30:31,891
¤¤ [ Humming Anthem ]

1314
01:30:57,552 --> 01:30:59,520
<i>[ Man ]
<i>Sir? Sir?</i>

1315
01:30:59,587 --> 01:31:01,851
- A ticket to London.
- <i>Single or return ?

1316
01:31:01,923 --> 01:31:04,892
- Single.
- <i>Two pound, eight and three, please.</i>

1317
01:31:04,959 --> 01:31:07,723
<i>[ Train Whistle Blows ]

1318
01:31:12,133 --> 01:31:15,660
- She'll look after you, son,
I'm telling you.
- Yeah.

1319
01:31:15,770 --> 01:31:20,469
- Fifteen shillings.
- You'll be all right.
Of course you will.

1320
01:31:20,575 --> 01:31:22,702
-What time's your train in the morning ?
-About six-ish.

1321
01:31:22,810 --> 01:31:25,870
<i>[ Woman ] Six-ish, is it ?
<i>She'll see you arrive on time.</i>

1322
01:31:25,980 --> 01:31:28,915
- <i>Have a nice breakfast</i>
<i>before you go, won't you ?
- <i>Of course I will.</i>

1323
01:31:28,983 --> 01:31:31,918
- <i>We'll look after him, won't we ?
- <i>He'll be all right.</i>

1324
01:31:31,986 --> 01:31:35,183
<i>You'll be all right. When will you</i>
<i>be back in country to see us ?

1325
01:31:35,256 --> 01:31:37,520
<i>[ Continues, Indistinct ]

1326
01:31:39,026 --> 01:31:42,826
- <i>[ Man Stammering ]
- That young man is blind drunk.

1327
01:31:42,930 --> 01:31:45,262
<i>What a shame.</i>
<i>That poor girl.</i>

1328
01:31:45,533 --> 01:31:48,525
[ Indistinct Muttering ]

1329
01:31:48,636 --> 01:31:52,003
<i>[ Girl ] You shouldn't drink,</i>
<i>and you wouldn't get like this!</i>

1330
01:31:52,106 --> 01:31:55,132
<i>[ Man ] Get that man in the guardhouse.</i>
<i>He'll feel great in the morning.</i>

1331
01:31:55,243 --> 01:31:57,768
[ Indistinct ]

1332
01:31:57,845 --> 01:32:01,576
Come on. Come on !

1333
01:32:01,682 --> 01:32:03,616
Ah !

1334
01:32:03,684 --> 01:32:06,244
<i>[ Panting ]

1335
01:32:06,320 --> 01:32:10,222
Oh, look what's crawled
out of the cheese !

1336
01:32:10,291 --> 01:32:12,225
Hello, Lisa.

1337
01:32:14,128 --> 01:32:16,790
From forest and lea we come.

1338
01:32:18,065 --> 01:32:20,898
Um, what happened
to Barbara, then ?

1339
01:32:20,968 --> 01:32:23,766
I don't know,
and I don't care.

1340
01:32:23,871 --> 01:32:26,203
You think you're somebody,
don't you ?

1341
01:32:26,307 --> 01:32:29,174
I'll tell you something.
You're not !

1342
01:32:29,277 --> 01:32:31,211
You're nobody.

1343
01:32:31,312 --> 01:32:35,043
I'm sorry. You can have
the ring, for all I care.

1344
01:32:35,149 --> 01:32:38,118
That ring ?
I wouldn't touch it.

1345
01:32:38,219 --> 01:32:41,279
Go on, get away.
You're just muck.

1346
01:32:42,823 --> 01:32:44,916
Come on, you.

1347
01:32:44,992 --> 01:32:47,290
Come on !

1348
01:32:47,361 --> 01:32:51,855
I go walking at night.
Left, right, left, right.

1349
01:32:51,966 --> 01:32:57,165
[ Man Grumbling, Indistinct ]

1350
01:33:18,693 --> 01:33:20,661
- Hi.
- I had to walk.

1351
01:33:20,761 --> 01:33:22,854
Oh, never mind.
Do you good.

1352
01:33:22,964 --> 01:33:25,956
Just missed the last bus.
I saw it going.

1353
01:33:26,067 --> 01:33:28,627
I turned the corner,
and there it was moving on.

1354
01:33:28,703 --> 01:33:30,762
- Oh, yeah.
- <i>[ Train Chugging ]

1355
01:33:30,871 --> 01:33:32,896
So I walked.

1356
01:33:33,007 --> 01:33:36,135
I went through the back streets.
I passed me old school.

1357
01:33:38,079 --> 01:33:40,013
There you are.

1358
01:33:40,081 --> 01:33:43,380
- Come on, you birds !
We can't wait all night !
- All right, we're here.

1359
01:33:43,651 --> 01:33:45,744
- Here you are.
- Do you have the tickets ?

1360
01:33:45,853 --> 01:33:47,753
- Ta.
- Ta.

1361
01:33:47,855 --> 01:33:51,086
Well, I seem to have
three face cloths and no toothbrush.

1362
01:33:51,192 --> 01:33:53,183
So I can borrow
yours, can't I ?

1363
01:33:53,294 --> 01:33:55,353
Yes.

1364
01:33:55,630 --> 01:33:58,030
[ Clears Throat ]

1365
01:33:58,132 --> 01:34:01,124
- <i>[ Annoying Chattering ]
- Have you got some cigarettes ?

1366
01:34:01,235 --> 01:34:05,228
- Yes, I've got some. Do you want one ?
- Uh, no.

1367
01:34:05,339 --> 01:34:07,967
It's stuffy in here.

1368
01:34:08,042 --> 01:34:10,169
Where are we going ?

1369
01:34:10,244 --> 01:34:13,042
Is it worth the money ?
I don't know.

1370
01:34:14,415 --> 01:34:16,315
<i>[ Chattering Continues ]

1371
01:34:16,417 --> 01:34:19,079
<i>[ Man ] Who's gonna kick for me</i>
<i>tomorrow night, then ?

1372
01:34:19,186 --> 01:34:21,916
- <i>[ Together ] Oh, not again!</i>
- <i>[ Woman ] You love that!</i>

1373
01:34:22,023 --> 01:34:24,014
<i>Yeah, but I had to leave,</i>
<i>didn't I ?

1374
01:34:24,125 --> 01:34:26,889
<i>I had to pay the rent.</i>
<i>And too many parties and all.</i>

1375
01:34:26,994 --> 01:34:28,962
<i>[ Laughter ]

1376
01:34:29,063 --> 01:34:32,294
<i>[ Man ] I hope you're not gonna talk</i>
<i>all night like last time.</i>

1377
01:34:32,400 --> 01:34:34,766
We can't get anything to eat
on this train, can we ?

1378
01:34:34,869 --> 01:34:37,394
Never mind. I've got
some sandwiches with me.

1379
01:34:37,672 --> 01:34:40,470
Well, would you like me
to get you a drink ?

1380
01:34:40,741 --> 01:34:42,868
No, not really.

1381
01:34:42,943 --> 01:34:45,002
- <i>[ Man ] Penzance.</i>
- <i>[ Woman ] Penzance ?

1382
01:34:45,079 --> 01:34:47,240
<i>Yeah, and then</i>
<i>we're back to Scotland.</i>

1383
01:34:47,348 --> 01:34:51,148
Wait a minute. There's
a milk machine on the station.

1384
01:34:51,252 --> 01:34:53,743
- <i>I can go and get you some.</i>
- I don't really want any.

1385
01:34:53,821 --> 01:34:55,880
No, i-i-it'll only take a minute.

1386
01:34:55,956 --> 01:34:57,890
Save me a place.

1387
01:34:57,958 --> 01:34:59,892
<i>Hurry up, Billy!</i>

1388
01:34:59,960 --> 01:35:03,157
I wonder if that kind lady
would let me share her gaff.

1389
01:35:03,264 --> 01:35:05,892
<i>[ Woman ] That kind lady'll give you</i>
<i>a punch up the throat.</i>

1390
01:35:05,966 --> 01:35:08,366
<i>[ Man Laughs ]

1391
01:35:10,738 --> 01:35:13,298
-Just gonna get some milk.
- You haven't got long.

1392
01:35:44,805 --> 01:35:47,330
<i>[ Conductor Blows Whistle ]

1393
01:35:50,111 --> 01:35:52,807
<i>[ Train Chugging ]

1394
01:35:52,913 --> 01:35:55,473
<i>[ Conductor Blows Whistle ]

1395
01:35:57,985 --> 01:36:00,476
<i>[ Train Whistle Blows ]

1396
